# .cursorrules for codebase-audit-mcp

## Project Context
This is a Python 3.12 MCP (Model Context Protocol) server called `codebase-audit-mcp`.
It performs static analysis of codebases: finds TODO markers, code smells, hardcoded secrets,
and generates health reports. Runs 100% locally, no external API calls in core functionality.

## Tech Stack
- Python 3.12
- mcp[http] вАФ official MCP Python SDK with FastMCP high-level API
- fastapi + uvicorn вАФ HTTP server
- No external API dependencies in core tools (ast, re, pathlib only)

## Architecture Rules
- All MCP tools are in `server/tools/` вАФ one file per tool
- Each tool file exports a single registration function: `register_{toolname}(mcp: FastMCP)`
- All tool functions are pure (no side effects) EXCEPT generate_health_report which writes to memory store
- Data models (TodoItem, SmellItem, etc.) live in `server/models.py` as Pydantic v2 models
- Constants (default tags, severity levels, ignore patterns) live in `server/config.py`
- The memory store for last report lives in `server/state.py` as a simple module-level dict

## Code Style
- Type hints everywhere вАФ no untyped functions
- Pydantic models for all return types вАФ tools return model.model_dump() as list/dict
- Docstrings on every tool function вАФ they become MCP tool descriptions
- Error handling: raise mcp.types.ToolError (not generic Exception) for user-facing errors
- Binary file detection: try decode as utf-8, skip on UnicodeDecodeError
- Always use pathlib.Path, never os.path string manipulation

## File Traversal Rules
- Always skip: __pycache__, .git, node_modules, .venv, venv, dist, build, .mypy_cache
- Skip binary extensions: .pyc, .pyo, .so, .dylib, .dll, .exe, .jpg, .png, .gif, .pdf, .zip
- Max file size to scan: 1 MB (skip larger files with a warning in output)

## Testing
- Tests are in `tests/` using pytest
- Each tool has its own test file: `tests/test_scan_todos.py` etc.
- Test fixtures (small code files with known issues) are in `tests/fixtures/`
- smoke test entrypoint is `server/smoke.py` вАФ it starts the server, calls /health, calls each tool

## Docker
- Base image: python:3.12-slim
- No root user in container
- ENTRYPOINT ["python", "main.py"], CMD ["serve"]
- "serve" starts uvicorn on 0.0.0.0:8000
- "smoke" runs server/smoke.py

## What NOT to do
- Do NOT use subprocess for core analysis (use ast and re modules)
- Do NOT store analysis results on disk (use in-memory state only)
- Do NOT make HTTP calls inside tools
- Do NOT use print() for logging вАФ use loguru module
- Do NOT hardcode paths вАФ always accept path as parameter
- Do NOT scan files outside the given path (no path traversal)
```

